<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203518>
    dc:description "FIGURE 38. The external morphology and polyps of Chrysogorgia geniculata (Wright & Studer, 1889). A, B. The same specimen in situ and after collection. C. A single terminal polyp under SEM. D. Tentacles with long pinnular sclerites under SEM. E. A part of branch under SEM. F. Basal polyp body wall under SEM. Scale bars: 5 cm (B); 1 mm (C); 500 μm (D–F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203518/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203520>
    dc:description "FIGURE 39. The sclerites of Chrysogorgia geniculata (Wright & Studer, 1889). A. Sclerites in pinnules. B. Sclerites in tentacle rachis. C. Sclerites at the base of tentacular part. D. Sclerites in the basal polyp body wall. E. Sclerites in coenenchyme. Scale bars: 300 μm (A, B, E, and C, D in the same scale, respectively)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203520/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

